          "And this time, even kings had to answer.",
          "EPILOGUE",
          "Dear Mortal,",
          "You have read to the end, so let us keep honest accounts, you and I.",
          "The girl kept the house until her braids went white. The library outlived her, and the lie outlived the library, and the locks outlived them all - seven of them, copper going green, holding a door in the dark long after everyone forgot what doors are for.",
          "Do not grieve too hard. The dead are only ledgers waiting to be read again, and souls, like debts, are never destroyed. They are transferred.",
